{
  "name": "Phantasmal Killer",
  "_id": "matSplPhantasKil",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You tap into the nightmares of a creature you can see within range and create an illusion of its deepest fears, visible only to that creature. The target makes a Wisdom saving throw. On a failed save, the target takes 4d10 Psychic damage and has Disadvantage on ability checks and attack rolls for the duration. On a successful save, the target takes half as much damage, and the spell ends.</p><p>For the duration, the target makes a [[/save ability=wis dc=@attributes.spelldc]] saving throw at the end of each of its turns. On a failed save, it takes the Psychic damage again. On a successful save, the spell ends.</p><p><strong>Using a Higher-Level Spell Slot.</strong>The damage increases by 1d10 for each spell slot level above 4.</p>",
